articles.author: Michelle Klampe
articles.title: Chemical analysis of natural CO₂ rise over the last 50,000 years shows that today's rate is 10 times faster - Phys.org
articles.description: Today's rate of atmospheric carbon dioxide increase is 10 times faster than at any other point in the past 50,000 years, researchers have found through a detailed chemical analysis of ancient Antarctic ice.
